887396cac92a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20our%20parenting%20style%20looks%20like%20in%20action%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20keep%20these%20values%20in%20mind%20during%20moments%20like%20yesterday.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20to%20enforce%20our%20authoritarian%20parenting%20style%20in%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20even%20though%20we%20were%20rushing%20to%20get%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%205-year-old%20son%20grabbed%20a%20box%20of%20mac%20and%20cheese%20off%20the%20shelf%20and%20threw%20it%20in%20our%20cart.%20While%20I%20put%20the%20box%20back%2C%20my%20husband%20told%20him%20it%20wasn't%20on%20our%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20son%20immediately%20started%20crying%20and%20yelling.%20He%20said%20we%20were%20mean%2C%20which%20I%20shut%20down%20right%20away.%20I%20told%20him%20he%20couldn't%20speak%20to%20us%20like%20that%20because%20he%20needed%20to%20respect%20us%2C%20and%20if%20he%20said%20it%20again%2C%20he'd%20lose%20TV%20privileges%20after%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crying%20continued%20as%20we%20walked%20down%20other%20aisles.%20When%20my%20husband%20shushed%20our%20son%2C%20he%20repeated%20that%20we%20were%20mean.%20When%20we%20got%20home%2C%20we%20stuck%20to%20our%20word%2C%20and%20he%20didn't%20get%20to%20watch%20%26quot%3BPaw%20Patrol.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20would%20have%20tried%20to%20quiet%20him%20in%20the%20store%20and%20eventually%20given%20up.%20Instead%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20explained%20why%20our%20son's%20language%20was%20wrong%20before%20enforcing%20the%20promised%20consequence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20our%20son%20pouted%20in%20his%20room%20later%20that%20night%2C%20we%20talked%20about%20why%20respecting%20us%20was%20important%2C%20how%20much%20we%20loved%20him%2C%20and%20how%20he%20should%20apologize.%20I%20know%20he'll%20learn%20over%20time%20that%20he%20can't%20do%20whatever%20he%20wants%2C%20which%20will%20make%20him%20a%20happier%20adult%20who%20people%20love%20to%20be%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%