ant-bars-food-delivery-hotel-salon-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etipping%20is%20more%20expected%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20where%20it%20could%20be%20optional%2C%26quot%3B%20Ted%20Rossman%2C%20a%20senior%20industry%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20do%20think%20the%20lines%20are%20blurring%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20businesses%20are%20looking%20to%20customers%20to%20make%20up%20some%20of%20the%20difference%20%E2%80%94%20that%20maybe%20they're%20reluctant%20to%20raise%20prices%20any%20higher%3B%20they're%20looking%20to%20supplement%20their%20employees'%20wages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERossman%20noted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-worker-feels-strange-asking-for-tips-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoffee%20shops%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20one%20place%20where%20tipping%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emay%20be%20more%20optional%2C%20while%20sit-down%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-cheap-bad-restaurant-tipping-best-worst-states-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-should-you-tip-for-delivery-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20delivery%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20two%20services%20where%20people%20should%20generally%20be%20tipping.%20Rossman%20noted%20salons%20or%20barbershops%20as%20another%20type%20of%20service%20where%20people%20should%20be%20tipping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-to-tip-tipping-etiquette-food-delivery-rideshare-service-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etipping%3C%2Fa%3E%20seems%20more%20prevalent%20these%20days%2C%20not%20everyone%20adds%20one%20to%20their%20payment.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20just%20now%20flat%20out%20refuse%20to%20tip%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20in%20that%20category%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20twice%20about%20how%20much%20I%20put%20in%20my%20tip%2C%26quot%3B%20Pam%20said%2C%20noting%20she%20thinks%20a%2015%25%20tip%20%26quot%3Bis%20more%20than%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Fcredit-cards%2Fnews%2Ftipping-culture-survey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBankrate%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20from%20April%2029%20to%20May%201%20found%20that%2067%25%20of%20US%20adult%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erespondents%20who%20go%20to%20sit-down%20restaurants%20always%20tip%20servers.%20Additionally%2C%2011%25%20said%20this%20for%20when%20they%20pick%20up%20takeout%2C%20and%2010%25%20said%20this%20for%20home%20services%20and%20repair%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETipping%20sentiment%20is%20different%20by%20generation.%20Rossman%20said%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20baby%20boomers%20in%20the%20survey%20were%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20there's%20too%20much%20tip%20creep%20and%20tipping%20culture's%20gotten%20out%20of%20control.%26quot%3B%20Rossman%20said%20the%20backlash%20against%20tipping%20could%20be%20because%20of%20high%20prices%2C%20tip%20creep%2C%20or%20people%20thinking%20they%20don't%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20spare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d8e7954-9a39-4b68-8da3-3574f319fee5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEven%20those%20who%20think%20tipping%20is%20out%20of%20control%20still%20think%20there%20are%20some%20places%20where%20it's%20appropriate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20retiree%2C%20Pam%20said%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20have%20had%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20eating%20out%20owing%20to%20big%20tips%20on%20top%20of%20elevated%20inflation%20while%20living%20on%20a%20fixed%20income.%20%26quot%3BMy%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20comfortable%2C%20there's%20no%20doubt%20about%20that%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20a%20fixed%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20Pam%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20life%20we%20planned%20for%20and%20saved%20for%20is%20inside%20that%20fixed%20income%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe's%20opposed%20to%20cues%20businesses%20have%20adopted%20that%20push%20patrons%20to%20leave%20gratuities.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20it%20should%20be%20a%20hundred%20percent%20up%20to%20the%20patron%20if%20they%20want%20to%20tip%20and%20not%20have%20all%20these%20suggested%20amounts%20and%20things%20printed%20on%20receipts%20and%20on%20the%20tablets%2C%26quot%3B%20Pam%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPam%20isn't%20the%20only%20one%20who%20feels%20tipping%20is%20out%20of%20control.%20Michael%20Sandberg%2C%2058%2C%20feels%20the%20tip%20jars%20he%20frequently%20sees%20sitting%20on%20the%20counters%20of%20retail%20establishments%20are%20uncalled%20for.%20He%20finds%20workers%20for%20other%20kinds%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-tipping-list-service-workers-beauty-technicians-tip-culture-us-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusinesses%20and%20services%20shouldn't%20be%20expecting%20a%20tip%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20think%20tipping%20is%20a%20good%20thing%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandberg%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20should%20get%20paid%20for%20their%20jobs%2C%20and%20why%20should%20I%20tip%20somebody%20to%20do%20their%20job%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20said%20instead%20of%20tips%2C%20restaurant%20servers%20should%20be%20paid%20a%20living%20wage.%20%26quot%3BIf%20that%20makes%20the%20price%20of%20the%20food%20go%20up%20at%20their%20restaurant%2C%20well%2C%20so%20be%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAsking%20your%20customers%20to%20pay%20your%20employees%20directly%20is%20obnoxious%20and%20not%20very%20cool%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20said%20he's%20%26quot%3Bway%20more%20likely%20to%20leave%20a%20tip%26quot%3B%20at%20small%20restaurants%20than%20larger%20ones.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20tip%20anywhere%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Sandberg%20doesn't%20see%20tipping%20as%20necessary%20if%20he's%20buying%20something%20himself%20because%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20extra%20service.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20have%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20order%20my%20food%20or%20to%20buy%20my%20product%2C%20you're%20not%20getting%20a%20tip%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222297ca1d-9d9e-4719-9808-ba26f9f1d745%5C%22%3ETipping%20could%20also%20be%20for%20exceptional%20service%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%2C%20who%20said%20he%20used%20to%20often%20go%20to%20restaurants%20and%20would%20tip%2010%25%2C%20noted%20a%20tip%20could%20be%20justified%20if%20you%20receive%20%26quot%3Bsome%20exceptionally%20great%20service%20somewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20a%20restaurant%20server%20doing%20an%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%20job%26quot%3B%20or%20going%20out%20of%20their%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPam%20recalled%20leaving%20more%20than%20the%20standard%20tip%20for%20a%20server%20because%20of%20especially%20great%20service%20that%20she%20wanted%20to%20acknowledge.%20She%20said%20the%20server%20%26quot%3Bwas%20so%20wonderful%26quot%3B%20with%20her%20grandchild%20%26quot%3Band%20brought%20her%20extra%20special%20cherries%20on%20her%20ice%20cream%20and%20things%20like%20that%20and%20played%20with%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20there%20are%20services%20Pam%20doesn't%20tip%20for%20and%20ones%20she%20does.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20never%20tip%20at%20a%20fast%20food%20establishment%20as%20a%20rule%2C%26quot%3B%20Pam%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20usually%20driving%20through%20and%20receive%20no%20service%20or%20pick%20up%20and%20take%20my%20order%20myself%20to%20a%20table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20an%20exception%20to%20Pam's%20rule.%20She%20noted%20she%20tipped%20a%20cleaner%20at%20a%20fast-food%20establishment.%20She%20said%20she%20saw%20this%20person%20%26quot%3Bon%20more%20than%20one%20occasion%20doing%20an%20exceptional%20job.%20She%20obviously%20took%20great%20pride%20in%20her%20work%20and%20I%20appreciated%20how%20immaculate%20she%20kept%20the%20restaurant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPam%20said%20she%20always%20tips%20at%20the%20nail%20salon%20she%20goes%20to%20%26quot%3Band%20for%20other%20personal%20one-on-one%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20if%20she%20were%20to%20ask%20%26quot%3Ba%20delivery%20driver%20to%20help%20with%20a%20heavy%20article%20into%20my%20house.%26quot%3B%20She%20also%20noted%20she%20wouldn't%20tip%20people%20who%20help%20bag%20items%20at%20grocery%20stores%20but%20said%20she%20always%20tips%20at%20a%20sit-down%20restaurant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20a%20tip%20should%20be%20when%20it's%20for%20%26quot%3Bextra%20service%20that%20someone%20gives%20you.%26quot%3B%20She%20gave%20the%20example%20of%20tipping%20a%20taxi%20driver%20who%20helps%20with%20your%20bags%2C%20opens%20the%20taxi's%20door%20for%20you%2C%20and%20gets%20you%20promptly%20to%20your%20destination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cf392fe9-a25c-495c-9a15-2f58f07a27bf%5C%22%3ETipping%20drivers%20is%20common%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2F2023%2F11%2F09%2Fservices-americans-do-and-dont-tip-for-and-how-much%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20found%2061%25%20of%20US%20adults%20who%20use%20rideshares%20or%20taxis%20often%20or%20always%20tip.%20While%20some%20people%20might%20give%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-tip-uber-lyft-driver-tipping-etiquette-rideshare-inflation-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etip%20to%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Sandberg%20doesn't%20really%20see%20that%20as%20always%20necessary.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20rideshare%20driver%20should%20get%20a%20tip%20if%20they%20go%20out%20of%20their%20way%20and%20make%20a%20real%20difference%20in%20the%20ride%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20said%20ride-hail%20drivers%20could%20receive%20more%20tips%20if%20%26quot%3Byou're%20in%20a%20very%20busy%20metropolitan%20or%20tourist%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20was%20an%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20driver%20several%20years%20ago.%20He%20recalled%20only%20once%20getting%20a%20tip%20and%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20only%20time%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20deserving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20went%20above%20and%20beyond%20my%20duties.%20I%20took%20all%20back%20roads%20to%20the%20airport%20when%20the%20freeway%20was%20closed%20due%20to%20a%20major%20accident%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rest%20of%20my%20rides%20were%20just%20doing%20my%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20business%20owner%20or%20customer%20willing%20to%20share%20your%20views%20and%20practices%20on%20tipping%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3EReach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-you-tip-restaurant-servers-drivers-rideshare-taxi-nail-salons-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721468222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6691a4228893442a51565cbb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-you-tip-restaurant-servers-drivers-rideshare-taxi-nail-salons-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20customers%20are%20fed%20up%20with%20expectations%20around%20tipping%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20have%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20order%20my%20food%20or%20to%20buy%20my%20product%2C%20you're%20not%20getting%20a%20tip.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%2