0defeat%20Russia%20and%20reclaim%20lost%20territory%2C%20according%20to%20two%20American%20experts.%20But%20only%20if%20the%20battered%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20is%20capable%20and%20willing%20to%20drastically%20change%20the%20way%20it%20fights%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSenior%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ukraine-could-get-air-superiority-use-f-16s-experts-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkrainian%20Armed%20Forces%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaders%20must%20rid%20themselves%20of%20the%20Soviet%2FRussian%20doctrine%20and%20tactics%2C%20techniques%2C%20and%20procedures%20in%20which%20they%20have%20been%20trained%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20David%20Deptula%20and%20Christopher%20Bowie%20in%20a%20report%20for%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOld%20habits%20die%20hard.%20They%20must%20be%20willing%20to%20embrace%20new%20concepts%20and%20training%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20a%20willingness%20to%20'rewrite%20the%20books'%20on%20military%20employment.%20Finally%2C%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20leadership%20must%20be%20incorporated%20into%20the%20Ukrainian%20General%20Staff%20to%20foster%20and%20facilitate%20integrated%2C%20all-domain%20concepts%2C%20planning%2C%20and%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%20is%20that%20it%20will%20not%20be%20easy%2C%26quot%3B%20Deptula%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20Air%20Force%20lieutenant%20general%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20take%20years%20for%20the%20Ukrainian%20military%20culture%20to%20shift%20from%20the%20model%20based%20on%20their%20Soviet%20military%20history%2C%20to%20Western%20military%20doctrine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoviet%20doctrine%20tended%20to%20be%20rigid%20and%20top-down%2C%20with%20commanders%20expected%20to%20stick%20to%20the%20plan%20rather%20than%20take%20initiative%20in%20response%20to%20opportunities%20or%20setbacks%20on%20the%20battlefield.%20Joint%20operations%20were%20lacking%3A%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%2C%20the%20Russian%20Air%20Force%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.japcc.org%2Farticles%2Frussian-air-forces-performance-in-ukraine-air-operations-the-fall-of-a-myth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efailed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20provide%20significant%20close%20air%20support%20and%20fighter%20cover%20to%20the%20ground%20troops.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-teaching-nato-air-forces-lessons-fighting-russia-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20air%20force%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20shown%20itself%20capable%20of%20devastating%20area%20bombardment%20but%20not%20the%20more%20precise%20strikes%20needed%20to%20defeat%20a%20moving%20enemy%20or%20take%20out%20its%20strongpoints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20for%20Ukraine%20is%20that%20many%20of%20its%20senior%20officers%20began%20their%20careers%20in%20the%20Soviet%20military%2C%20were%20trained%20in%20Soviet%20military%20academies%2C%20and%20created%20the%20nation's%20armed%20forces%20in%20the%20Soviet%20image.%20They%20tend%20to%20revert%20to%20this%20background%20when%20they%20struggle%20with%20advice%20from%20Western%20militaries%2C%20as%20happened%20amid%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-ukrainian-counteroffensive-ran-into-trouble-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20counter-offensive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20changing%20as%20younger%20officers%20rise%2C%20but%20embracing%20a%20radically%20different%20military%20culture%20and%20mindset%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20during%20wartime%20%E2%80%94%20is%20extremely%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20has%20struggled%20with%20its%20own%20bureaucratic%20problems%20that%20hindered%20effective%20operations.%20For%20example%2C%20Deptula%20pointed%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwarontherocks.com%2F2023%2F09%2Fgoldwater-ripples-how-defense-reform-made-the-fighting-force-more-diplomatic%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoldwater-Nichols%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201986%2C%20which%20aimed%20to%20eliminate%20rivalry%20between%20the%20US%20armed%20services%20that%20hampered%20joint%20operations%20(such%20as%20incompatible%20radios%2C%20which%20prevented%20Army%20troops%20from%20communicating%20with%20Navy%20ships%20during%20the%201982%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.militaryaerospace.com%2Fcommunications%2Farticle%2F16710975%2Fsometimes-it-takes-a-disaster-to-make-people-communicate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvasion%20of%20Grenada%3C%2Fa%3E).%20To%20spur%20jointness%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%20was%20given%20more%20power%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20service%20chiefs%2C%20who%20also%20lost%20operational%20control%20over%20their%20forces%20in%20favor%20of%20regional%20combatant%20commands.%20Promotion%20to%20general%20or%20admiral%20also%20required%20prior%20experience%20in%20joint%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%2040%20years%20after%20Goldwater-Nichols%2C%20interservice%20rivalry%20%E2%80%94%20from%20football%20to%20funding%20%E2%80%94%20has%20hardly%20disappeared%20from%20the%20American%20military.%20But%20at%20least%20the%20US%20armed%20services%20have%20become%20accustomed%20to%20joint%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20something%20that%20Ukraine%20must%20do%20to%20win%2C%20or%20even%20just%20to%20survive.%20Facing%20superior%20Russian%20numbers%20and%20resources%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20military%20must%20extract%20maximum%20efficiency%20from%20its%20forces.%20This%20means%20a%20flexible%2C%20coordinated%20style%20of%20warfare.%20For%20example%2C%20ground-based%20artillery%20and%20rockets%20can%20destroy%20Russian%20air%20defense%20systems%2C%20which%20enables%20Ukraine's%20air%20force%20to%20operate%20over%20the%20battlefield%2C%20and%20thus%20provide%20close%20air%20support%20to%20the%20army.%20Missions%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-air-force-far-from-ready-for-mission-taiwan-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclose%20air%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20a%20major%20impact%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20but%20Ukraine%20must%20shift%20to%20more%20coordination%20between%20its%20air%20controllers%20and%20air%20defense%20crews%20or%20risk%20shooting%20down%20its%20own%20jets%2C%20the%20Mitchell%20paper%20emphasizes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20others%20have%20warned%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ff-16-to-ukraine-most-dangerous-battlefield-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EF-16s%20are%20very%20vulnerable%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Ukraine's%20contested%20airspace%20and%20that%20the%20country%20may%20not%20be%20getting%20enough%20to%20sustain%20the%20losses%20that%20missions%20to%20push%20back%20Russian%20forces%20could%20entail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20reforms%20won't%20be%20easy.%20%26quot%3BIt%20took%20the%20US%20military%20decades%20to%20adopt%20to%20the%20tenets%20of%20joint%20force%20operations%20and%20the%20joint%20structure%20ensconced%20in%20the%20Goldwater-Nichols%20Act%20of%201986%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Deptula.%20%26quot%3BSome%20would%20say%20that%20some%20services%2C%20like%20the%20Army%20and%20Marines%2C%20never%20fully%20adopted.%20That%20said%2C%20this%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20the%20Ukrainian%20military%20can't%20adopt%20for%20certain%20operations%20immediately.%20They%20will%20have%20to%20if%20they%20are%20to%20achieve%20advantage%20over%20the%20disproportionate%20size%20advantage%20that%20Russia%20holds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeptula%20believes%20the%20desire%20to%20reform%20Ukraine's%20military%20is%20there%2C%20at%20least%20at%20the%20lower%20levels.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20take%20a%20combination%20of%20leadership%20push%2C%20new%20generation%20officer%20pull%2C%20and%20a%20collective%20desire%20to%20reform%20to%20accept%20and%20institute%20a%20Western%20way%20of%20war%20relative%20to%20the%20