omy%20and%20to%20de-escalate%20the%20situation%20when%20it%20happens.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20morning%2C%20when%20Oscar%20climbed%20on%20top%20of%20a%20four-foot%20wall%20separating%20the%20pedestrian%20path%20from%20the%20natural%20coastal%20environment%2C%20I%20assessed%20the%20situation.%20Was%20that%20wall%20built%20for%20people%20to%20be%20walking%20on%20it%3F%20Probably%20not.%20But%20were%20there%20any%20signs%20explicitly%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20forbidden%3F%20No.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20was%20Oscar%20putting%20himself%20in%20any%20sort%20of%20danger%3F%20No%20again.%20The%20wall%20was%20low%20and%20wide%20enough%20that%20he%20was%20unlikely%20to%20get%20hurt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20so%2C%20another%20tourist%20shouted%20at%20me%20to%20get%20my%20son%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202402d51-a15b-494a-bbf0-7e93f152841d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20someone%20tells%20me%20how%20to%20parent%2C%20I%20just%20smile%20and%20pretend%20I%20don't%20speak%20English%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20the%20outside%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fpermissive-parenting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3Blow%20demand%26quot%3B%20parenting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20can%20look%20overly%20permissive%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20arguably%2C%20for%20a%20typical%20kid%2C%20it%20might%20be.%20But%20we're%20not%20talking%20about%20a%20typical%20kid.%20We're%20talking%20about%20a%20kid%20who'd%20rather%20run%20straight%20into%20traffic%20than%20follow%20a%20rule%20he's%20deemed%20unjust.%20A%20kid%20that%20won't%20listen%20to%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20I%20said%20so.%26quot%3B%20Who%20once%20%E2%80%94%20feeling%20rushed%20into%20the%20taxi%20cab%20so%20that%20we'd%20make%20our%20flight%20%E2%80%94%20got%20so%20dysregulated%20that%20he%20tried%20to%20open%20the%20car%20door%20and%20throw%20himself%20out%20of%20the%20moving%20vehicle%20on%20the%20highway.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20explain%20all%20this%20to%20strangers.%20I%20can't%20explain%20to%20every%20person%20we%20pass%20why%20my%20kid%20isn't%20wearing%20shoes%20on%20a%20Manhattan%20sidewalk%20or%20why%20I%20won't%20admonish%20him%20when%20he%20doesn't%20politely%20return%20their%20greeting%20(social%20mores%20are%20experienced%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdemand%26quot%3B).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20don't%20owe%20these%20strangers%2C%20or%20anyone%2C%20any%20explanation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247f4cf2d-c221-4680-a956-b2e41daaafef%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20people's%20comfort%20isn't%20my%20priority%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHeading%20back%20to%20the%20room%2C%20Oscar%20eyed%20a%20shelf%20of%20crystal%20animals%20prominently%20displayed%20in%20the%20gift%20shop%20window.%20I%20was%20acutely%20aware%20of%20the%20salesperson's%20hypervigilance%20from%20the%20moment%20we%20entered.%20Before%20Oscar%20even%20touched%20the%20little%20glass%20turtle%20%E2%80%94%20which%20I%20was%20fully%20prepared%20to%20let%20him%20do%20%E2%80%94%20the%20salesperson%20launched%20herself%20at%20him%20and%20me%2C%20shouting%2C%20%26quot%3BHe%20can't%20touch%20that!%20It's%20glass!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20second%20child%20responded%20how%20a%20neurotypical%20child%20naturally%20would.%20Molly%20froze%20and%20moved%20closer%20to%20me.%20But%20Oscar's%20nervous%20system%20perceives%20situations%20like%20these%20as%20a%20serious%20threat%2C%20and%20it%20tells%20him%20to%20fight%20or%20run.%20He%20exited%20the%20store%20at%20a%20hundred%20miles%20an%20hour%2C%20headed%20who-knows-where.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOscar%20has%20a%20one-on-one%20aide%20at%20school%20because%20of%20this%20behavior%2C%20but%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20help%20when%20we%20travel%2C%20and%20there%20have%20been%20times%20when%20I've%20had%20to%20temporarily%20abandon%20my%20neurotypical%20child%20to%20chase%20after%20my%20son.%20Thankfully%2C%20that%20morning%2C%20Molly%20was%20agreeable.%20She%20let%20me%20scoop%20her%20up%2C%20and%20we%20were%20out%20the%20door%2C%20just%20in%20time%20to%20see%20which%20direction%20he%20turned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222973cdd5-34b6-49fd-88ae-8c3cbbbf927f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3ESurrounded%20by%20nature%2C%20he%20is%20immediately%20more%20at%20ease%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoments%20later%2C%20I%20found%20Oscar%20in%20the%20tropical%20gardens%20and%20bird%20sanctuary%2C%20a%20captivating%20natural%20space%20filled%20with%20lush%20greenery%20and%20wildlife.%20His%20body%20was%20calm.%20He%20was%20back%20in%20control%20of%20himself%20and%20curious.%20I%20watched%20as%20he%20cautiously%20crossed%20the%20habitat%20toward%20an%20enormous%20turtle.%20There%20are%20no%20other%20tourists%20around%2C%20just%20a%20handful%20of%20bemused%20staff%20people%20watching%20him%20pick%20the%20animal%20up%2C%20just%20as%20he%20once%20learned%20to%20do%20at%20a%20turtle%20sanctuary%20in%20Sri%20Lanka.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20should%20stop%20him%2C%20probably%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20think.%20%26quot%3BBut%20why%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20you%20get%20in%20my%20son's%20way%2C%20things%20can%20go%20spectacularly%20bad.%20But%20when%20you%20get%20out%20of%20it%2C%20magic%20happens.%20One%20thing's%20for%20sure%3A%20traveling%20with%20my%20neurodivergent%20kid%20is%20never%20a%20dull%20moment.%20And%20actually%2C%20that's%20wonderful.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraveling-with-neurodivergent-child-can-be-hard-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721464262000%2C