e%20personally%20find%20the%20taste%20to%20be%20slightly%20better%20as%20the%20food%20is%20cooked%20slowly%20and%20the%20taste%20of%20the%20vegetable%20is%20retained%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20limitation%20of%20the%20set%20up%2C%20Reva%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20do%20most%20of%20the%20cooking%20in%20the%20solar%20cookers%2C%20we%20have%20also%20kept%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(stove)%20as%20a%20backup%20for%20cloudy%20and%20rainy%20days.%20We%20collect%20firewood%20from%20trees%20around%20our%20house%20and%20also%20use%20coconut%20shells%20and%20cow%20dung%20cakes%20as%20fuel.%20We%20use%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eonly%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20backup%20for%20cooking%20that%20they%20use%20during%20cloudy%20days%20and%20at%20night%20is%20their%20stored%20solar%20energy.%20Their%20house%20has%20a%20small%20850%20VA%20solar%20inverter%20that%20delivers%20enough%20charge%20for%20low-wattage%20electrical%20appliances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20fondly%20talks%20about%20how%20she%20repurposed%20and%20converted%20an%20old%20box-type%20solar%20cooker%20into%20a%20food%20dehydrator.%20They%20use%20it%20to%20dehydrate%20and%20preserve%20excess%20fruits%20when%20they%20have%20a%20bounty.%20The%20contraption%20is%20also%20used%20for%20roasting%20grains%2C%20nuts%20and%20even%20drying%20homegrown%20turmeric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reva%20also%20dehydrates%20excess%20fruits%20in%20sunlight.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2